[2026-03-11T21:25:46Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VgKT2HRKQWwdGh23Lxewca","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me create a comprehensive analysis document:\n\n## Cloche Project Structure and Architecture - Comprehensive Exploration\n\nBased on a thorough examination of the codebase, here's the complete technical overview of the Cloche system:\n\n---\n\n## **1. OVERALL PROJECT STRUCTURE**\n\n### Top-Level Directory Layout\n```\n/workspace/\n├── cmd/                      # Binary entry points (3 binaries)\n│   ├── cloche/              # CLI client (short-lived)\n│   ├── cloched/             # Daemon (long-running)\n│   └── cloche-agent/        # Container entrypoint (autonomous)\n├── internal/                # Core application logic\n│   ├── domain/              # Domain types (Run, Step, Workflow)\n│   ├── ports/               # Interface definitions (RunStore, ContainerRuntime, etc.)\n│   ├── adapters/            # Concrete implementations\n│   ├── host/                # Host workflow executor\n│   ├── engine/              # Workflow execution engine\n│   ├── dsl/                 # DSL parser & lexer\n│   ├── config/              # Configuration loading\n│   ├── agent/               # Agent runner for container\n│   ├── protocol/            # Result markers & status messages\n│   └── logstream/           # Unified log streaming\n├── .cloche/                 # Project-specific config\n│   ├── develop.cloche       # Container workflows\n│   ├── host.cloche          # Host orchestration workflows\n│   ├── config.toml          # Project configuration\n│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image definition\n│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates\n│   └── overrides/           # Files to override in container\n├── api/                     # gRPC protobuf definitions (auto-generated)\n├── docs/                    # Documentation\n├── examples/                # Example projects\n└── go.mod / go.sum          # Go dependencies\n```\n\n---\n\n## **2. THE THREE BINARIES**\n\n### **2.1 `cloche` (CLI Client)**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n**Design**: Short-lived CLI that connects to daemon via gRPC over Unix socket or TCP.\n\n**Commands**:\n- `init` - Initialize a Cloche project (no daemon needed)\n- `health` - Show project health (no daemon needed)\n- `run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]` - Launch workflow\n- `status <run-id>` - Check run status\n- `logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]` - Stream logs\n- `poll <run-id>` - Wait for completion\n- `list [--all]` - List recent runs\n- `stop <run-id>` - Stop running workflow\n- `delete <container-or-run-id>` - Delete retained container\n- `loop [--max <n>]` / `loop stop` - Manage orchestration loop\n- `shutdown` - Shut down daemon\n\n**gRPC Connection**:\n- Default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`\n- Configurable via `CLOCHE_ADDR` environment variable\n- Uses insecure credentials (local socket)\n\n---\n\n### **2.2 `cloched` (Daemon)**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n**Design**: Long-running server that manages container lifecycle, persists state, and executes host workflows.\n\n**Key Responsibilities**:\n1. **Listens on gRPC** (configurable via `CLOCHE_LISTEN`, default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n2. **HTTP Dashboard** (optional, via `CLOCHE_HTTP`, default: none)\n3. **SQLite Store** (configurable via `CLOCHE_DB`, default: `cloche.db`)\n4. **Container Runtime** (Docker or local, configurable via `CLOCHE_RUNTIME`)\n5. **Auto-run Active Projects** - At startup, scans for projects with `active = true` and runs their host workflows\n6. **Evolution Trigger** - Optional self-improvement system triggered after runs\n\n**Key Classes**:\n- `ClocheServer` (gRPC server implementation in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n  - Implements `RunWorkflow()`, `ListRuns()`, `GetStatus()`, `StreamLogs()`, etc.\n  - Manages run tracking via in-memory `map[string]string` (runID → containerID)\n  - Manages orchestration loops via `map[string]*host.Loop` (projectDir → Loop)\n\n---\n\n### **2.3 `cloche-agent` (Container Entrypoint)**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n\n**Design**: Autonomous agent that runs inside container, parses workflow DSL, and executes steps.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Receives workflow file path as arg: `cloche-agent /workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche`\n2. Reads `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` from environment (set by daemon before container start)\n3. Creates `RunnerConfig` and `Runner`\n4. Parses workflow DSL (container location)\n5. Creates adapters:\n   - `generic.Adapter` - for `script` and `agent` steps with `run` config\n   - `prompt.Adapter` - for `agent` steps with `prompt` config\n6. Sets up unified log stream and status writer\n7. Runs workflow via `engine.Engine`\n8. Emits JSON status messages to stdout (parsed by daemon)\n\n---\n\n## **3. DOMAIN TYPES** (`/workspace/internal/domain/`)\n\n### **3.1 Run State Machine**\n**File**: `run.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunState string\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState\n    ActiveSteps    []string              // Currently executing steps\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution      // Complete history\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string                // Absolute path to project root\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string                // Docker container ID (if container run)\n    BaseSHA        string                // Git HEAD at run start\n    ContainerKept  bool                  // true if container retained after completion\n    Title          string                // One-line summary of work\n    IsHost         bool                  // true for host workflow runs\n    ParentRunID    string                // ID of parent host run (for child container runs)\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string                  // Output state for results\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `NewRun(id, workflowName)` - Create new run\n- `Start()` - Transition to Running, set StartedAt\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)` - Add to ActiveSteps, create StepExecution\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` - Remove from ActiveSteps, complete StepExecution\n- `Complete(state)` - Transition to terminal state, set CompletedAt\n- `Fail(msg)` - Mark as failed with error message\n\n---\n\n### **3.2 Workflow & Step Types**\n**File**: `workflow.go`\n\n```go\ntype StepType string\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    = \"agent\"      // LLM or script-based agent\n    StepTypeScript   = \"script\"     // Shell command\n    StepTypeWorkflow = \"workflow\"   // Dispatch container workflow (host only)\n)\n\ntype WorkflowLocation string\nconst (\n    LocationContainer = \"container\"  // Runs inside Docker\n    LocationHost      = \"host\"       // Runs on host machine\n)\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType\n    Results []string                 // Declared outcomes (e.g., \"success\", \"fail\", \"needs_review\")\n    Config  map[string]string        // Step-specific config\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire                 // Result routing\n    Collects  []Collect              // Fanin synchronization\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string      // Workflow-level config (e.g., \"container.image\")\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string\n    Result    string\n    To        string\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping        // Environment variable extraction\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n    EnvVar string\n    Path   OutputPath                // JSON path navigation\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment           // Field access or array indexing\n}\n```\n\n**Key Workflow Config Keys**:\n- Container-level: `container.image`, `container.agent_command`, `container.agent_args`\n- Host-level: `host.agent_command`, `host.agent_args`\n\n**Step Config Keys**:\n- `prompt` - Prompt template (agent steps)\n- `run` - Shell command (script/agent steps)\n- `agent_command` - Agent fallback chain (comma-separated)\n- `agent_args` - Explicit agent arguments\n- `results` - Declared result names (redundant with Step.Results)\n- `max_attempts` - Retry limit\n- `timeout` - Step timeout (e.g., \"30m\")\n- `feedback` - Include validation output in agent prompt\n- `workflow_name` - Workflow to dispatch (host only)\n- `prompt_step` - Override previous step for prompt source\n\n---\n\n### **3.3 Run ID Generation**\n**File**: `namegen.go`\n\n```go\n// Format: <workflow>-<adjective>-<noun>-<hex>\n// Example: develop-swift-oak-a1b2\nfunc GenerateRunID(workflowName string) string {\n    adj := adjectives[mathrand.Intn(len(adjectives))]\n    noun := nouns[mathrand.Intn(len(nouns))]\n    var b [2]byte\n    rand.Read(b[:])\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s-%s-%s\", workflowName, adj, noun, hex.EncodeToString(b[:]))\n}\n```\n\nAdjectives: swift, bright, calm, dark, eager, fair, grand, happy, keen, lush, bold, cool, deft, firm, glad, warm, wild, wise, crisp, fresh, light, quick, sharp, quiet, vivid, brave, clear, gentle, proud, steady\n\nNouns: oak, elm, fox, hawk, lake, pine, reef, sage, vale, wolf, bear, cove, dale, fern, glen, hare, jade, lark, moss, nest, peak, reed, star, tide, vine, birch, brook, crane, drift, flint\n\n---\n\n## **4. PORTS & ADAPTERS** (Hexagonal Architecture)\n\n### **4.1 RunStore Interface**\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\n// SQLite Adapter: /workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go\n```\n\n**Database Schema** (SQLite):\n- `runs` table: id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id\n- `step_executions` table: id, run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n- `log_files` table: id, run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at\n- `merge_queue` table: run_id, branch, project, status, enqueued_at, completed_at\n- `evolution_log` table: id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, created_at, classification, changes_json, knowledge_delta\n\n---\n\n### **4.2 ContainerRuntime Interface**\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`\n\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ContainerConfig struct {\n    Image        string\n    WorkflowName string\n    ProjectDir   string\n    NetworkAllow []string\n    RunID        string\n    Cmd          []string              // Default: [\"cloche-agent\", WorkflowName]\n}\n\n// Docker Adapter: /workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go\n// Local Adapter: /workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go\n```\n\n---\n\n### **4.3 AgentAdapter Interface**\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Implementations**:\n- `prompt.Adapter` - Wraps Claude Code or other agents\n- `generic.Adapter` - Wraps shell scripts\n\n---\n\n## **5. WORKFLOW EXECUTION MODEL**\n\n### **5.1 Container Workflow Execution (Daemon → Container → Agent)**\n\n**Flow**:\n1. User: `cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"...\"`\n2. CLI → gRPC: `RunWorkflow()`\n3. Daemon: Creates Run (pending), launches background goroutine\n4. Background: Ensures image, starts container via Docker\n5. Container:\n   - Copies `/workspace/` from host\n   - Applies `.cloche/overrides/` on top\n   - Copies Claude auth files (`.claude/`, `.claude.json`)\n   - Runs as root, then `su agent -s /bin/sh` for safety\n   - Executes: `cloche-agent /workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche`\n6. Agent (in container):\n   - Parses DSL\n   - Walks step graph via `engine.Engine`\n   - For each step: executes via appropriate adapter\n   - Emits JSON status messages to stdout\n7. Daemon: Reads status messages, persists Run state to SQLite\n8. Daemon: When container exits, extracts `.cloche/output/` to host\n9. Daemon: Creates git branch `cloche/<run-id>` with results\n10. Run transitions to terminal state\n\n---\n\n### **5.2 Host Workflow Execution (Daemon → Host Steps)**\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Daemon starts (or via `cloche loop` command)\n2. Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` - may contain multiple workflows (main, finalize, etc.)\n3. Creates `Runner` with callbacks\n4. Runner executes via `Executor.Execute()` for each step type:\n   - **Script**: Shell command on host machine\n   - **Workflow**: Dispatches container workflow, blocks until complete\n   - **Agent**: Calls prompt adapter on host (Claude Code)\n5. Step outputs stored in `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n6. Wires pass outputs as environment variables to next steps\n\n---\n\n## **6. STEP EXECUTION & ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES**\n\n### **6.1 Container Run Environment**\n\n**Set by Daemon (Docker)**:\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<run-id>` - Passed via `-e` to `docker create`\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` - Passed if set on host\n- Additional via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` env var (comma-separated KEY=VALUE)\n\n**Set by Container Init Script**:\n- None beyond above\n\n**Available to Agent Steps**:\n- From step config: `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `prompt`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`\n- From workflow config: `container.agent_command`, `container.agent_args`\n\n---\n\n### **6.2 Host Run Environment**\n\n**Set by Executor for Script Steps**:\n```go\ncmd.Env = append(os.Environ(),\n    \"CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR=\"+e.ProjectDir,          // Always project root\n    \"CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT=\"+e.stepOutputPath(step.Name),\n    \"CLOCHE_TASK_ID=\"+e.TaskID,                  // If set by daemon loop\n    \"CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT=\"+prevOutput,            // Previous step output\n    ...mappedEnvVars...                          // From output mappings\n)\n```\n\n**Available to Agent Steps (Host)**:\n- From `Agent` adapter config: `agent_command`, `agent_args`\n- From step config: `prompt`, `prompt_step`\n- Run ID written to: `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n\n---\n\n### **6.3 Output Mappings & Environment Variables**\n\n**Mechanism**: Wires can define `OutputMap` to extract step output as env vars for next step.\n\n**Example DSL**:\n```\nstep1 -> success -> step2 {\n  env: MY_DATA { .result }        // Extract JSON field\n}\n```\n\n**Path Evaluation**: JSONPath-like syntax in `OutputPath.Evaluate()`\n- No segments: return raw output as string\n- `.field`: object field access\n- `[index]`: array indexing\n- Supports nested: `.users[0].name`\n\n---\n\n### **6.4 Result Markers**\n\n**Format**: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` on its own line (anywhere in output)\n\n**Extraction** (`protocol.ExtractResult()`):\n- Scans all output lines\n- Keeps last CLOCHE_RESULT marker encountered\n- Strips all marker lines from clean output\n- Returns: (resultName, cleanOutput, found)\n\n**Usage**:\n- Script: Echo marker to indicate non-standard result\n- Agent: Built into prompt instructions\n\n---\n\n## **7. LOG SYSTEM**\n\n### **7.1 Unified Log (Container)**\n**File**: `.cloche/<run-id>/full.log` (created by agent via `logstream.Writer`)\n\n**Contents**: Structured log entries combining:\n- Status markers (step started/completed)\n- Script output\n- LLM output (from Claude Code)\n\n---\n\n### **7.2 Per-Step Logs (Container)**\n**Files**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.log`\n\n**Contents**: \n- Scripts: Combined stdout/stderr (without result marker)\n- Agents: Raw output from agent command\n\n---\n\n### **7.3 Container Full Log**\n**File**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/container.log`\n\n**Contents**: Full `docker logs` output (unfiltered, all steps)\n\n---\n\n### **7.4 History Log (Host)**\n**File**: `.cloche/history.log` (permanent record)\n\n**Format**:\n```\n[2026-03-11T21:18:00Z] workflow:start develop\n\n[2026-03-11T21:18:15Z] step:plan result:success\n  | Generated 3 ideas\n  | 1. Add feature X\n  | 2. Fix bug Y\n\n[2026-03-11T21:18:20Z] step:implement result:success (agent)\n\n[2026-03-11T21:20:00Z] workflow:end develop result:succeeded\n```\n\n---\n\n## **8. ORCHESTRATION LOOP (Host Workflow Automation)**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n### **8.1 Three-Phase Loop**\n\n```\nLoop:\n  1. List Tasks (via list-tasks workflow)\n     └─ Returns: []{id, status, title, description, metadata}\n  \n  2. For each open task (up to MaxConcurrent):\n     └─ Run main workflow (passes CLOCHE_TASK_ID)\n  \n  3. After main completes:\n     └─ Run finalize workflow (receives mainResult outcome)\n\n  Deduplication: Don't re-assign same task within DedupTimeout (default: 5min)\n```\n\n### **8.2 Legacy Loop**\n\n```\nLoop:\n  1. (Optional) List tasks via TaskAssigner\n  2. For each open task (up to MaxConcurrent):\n     └─ Run single workflow (passes CLOCHE_TASK_ID)\n  3. (No finalize phase)\n```\n\n### **8.3 Configuration**\n\n```go\ntype LoopConfig struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MaxConcurrent int\n    StaggerDelay  time.Duration     // Delay between consecutive launches\n    DedupTimeout  time.Duration     // Task reassignment suppression window\n}\n```\n\n**Config Source** (`.cloche/config.toml`):\n```toml\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 2\nstagger_seconds = 1.0\nlist_tasks_command = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\ndedup_seconds = 300.0\n```\n\n---\n\n## **9. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (HOST & CONTAINER)**\n\n### **Key Variables**\n\n| Variable | Set By | Used By | Value |\n|----------|--------|---------|-------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | Daemon → Docker `-e` | Agent (reads, unsetsenv) | Generated run ID |\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Executor | Host scripts | Project root directory |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Executor | Host scripts | Path to step output file |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Executor | Host scripts | Task ID from loop |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Executor | Host scripts | Previous step output |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Container env | Agent runner | Fallback agent chain |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Host | Container | API key for Claude |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | Host | Docker | Comma-separated KEY=VALUE |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | Host | Docker | Comma-separated host:container paths |\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | User | CLI | gRPC server address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | User | CLI | HTTP dashboard address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | User | Daemon | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | User | Daemon | gRPC listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | User | Daemon | Default container image |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | User | Daemon | \"docker\" or \"local\" |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | User | Daemon | Path to cloche-agent binary |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | User | Daemon | Command for evolution |\n\n---\n\n## **10. CONTEXT & STATE MANAGEMENT**\n\n### **10.1 Run Context**\n\nEach run has:\n- **Run ID** - Unique identifier\n- **Workflow Name** - Entry point workflow\n- **Project Directory** - Absolute path to project\n- **Step Execution History** - All steps executed, their results, timing\n- **Output Directory** - `.cloche/<run-id>/output/` for step outputs\n- **BaseSHA** - Git HEAD when run started (for result branch creation)\n\n### **10.2 Per-Run State Storage**\n\n**On Disk**:\n- `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` - User prompt (for agent steps)\n- `.cloche/<run-id>/output/` - Step outputs, full log, container log\n- `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>` - Retry counter per step (container only)\n- `.cloche/history.log` - Permanent workflow event log (host only)\n\n**In SQLite**:\n- `runs` table - Run metadata\n- `step_executions` table - Execution history\n- `log_files` table - Log file index\n\n**In Memory (Daemon)**:\n- `ClocheServer.runIDs` - Run ID → Container ID mapping\n- `ClocheServer.loops` - Project Dir → Orchestration Loop\n\n---\n\n### **10.3 Output Path Conventions**\n\n```\nproject-root/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── <run-id>/\n│   │   ├── prompt.txt                  # Agent prompt input\n│   │   └── output/\n│   │       ├── full.log                # Unified log (container only)\n│   │       ├── container.log           # Full docker logs\n│   │       ├── <step-name>.log         # Per-step output\n│   │       ├── llm-<step-name>.log     # Copy of agent step log\n│   │       ├── <step-name>.out         # Host executor step output\n│   │       ├── full.log                # Concatenated output (agent)\n│   │       └── merged-content.md       # Git merge result (host)\n│   ├── attempt_count/                  # Retry counters (container)\n│   │   └── <step-name>\n│   ├── output/                         # Legacy: per-step logs\n│   │   └── <step-name>.log\n│   └── history.log                     # Permanent event log (host)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **11. DSL PARSER & CONFIGURATION**\n\n### **11.1 DSL Syntax**\n\n**File**: `*.cloche` (e.g., `develop.cloche`, `host.cloche`)\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step plan {\n    type: agent\n    results: success, needs_clarification\n    prompt: file(\"prompts/plan.md\")\n  }\n\n  step implement {\n    type: agent\n    results: success, fail\n    prompt: file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    feedback: true\n    max_attempts: 3\n    timeout: 60m\n    agent_command: claude\n    agent_args: -p --verbose\n  }\n\n  step validate {\n    type: script\n    results: pass, fail\n    run: bash .cloche/scripts/validate.sh\n  }\n\n  plan -> success -> implement\n  implement -> success -> validate\n  plan -> needs_clarification -> done\n  validate -> pass -> done\n  validate -> fail -> abort\n\n  collect { all plan:success, implement:success, validate:pass } -> finalize\n\n  container {\n    image: cloche-agent:latest\n    agent_command: claude\n    agent_args: -p --verbose\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Parser Location**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `Parse(input, opts...)` - Parse single workflow\n- `ParseForContainer()` - Parse with container location\n- `ParseForHost()` - Parse with host location\n- `ParseAllForHost()` - Parse multiple workflows from host.cloche\n\n---\n\n### **11.2 Configuration File**\n\n**File**: `.cloche/config.toml` (per-project)\n\n```toml\nactive = true                           # Auto-run at daemon startup\n\n[daemon]\nlisten = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\nhttp = \"localhost:8080\"\nimage = \"cloche-agent:latest\"\ndb = \"cloche.db\"\nruntime = \"docker\"                      # or \"local\"\nagent_path = \"/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\"\nllm_command = \"claude code --service evolution\"\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = true\ndebounce_seconds = 30\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"               # low, medium, high\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 2\nstagger_seconds = 1.0\nlist_tasks_command = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\ndedup_seconds = 300.0\n```\n\n**Global Config**: `~/.config/cloche/config` (daemon defaults)\n\n---\n\n## **12. INITIALIZATION & STARTUP**\n\n### **12.1 Daemon Startup** (`cloched`)\n\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config` (or defaults)\n2. Initialize SQLite store (with WAL, busy_timeout, single connection)\n3. Sweep stale runs (mark pending/running as failed)\n4. Initialize container runtime (Docker or local)\n5. Create gRPC server\n6. Scan projects for `active = true`, auto-run host workflows\n7. Set up evolution trigger (if LLM command configured)\n8. Listen on gRPC and HTTP\n\n### **12.2 Container Start**\n\n**Docker**:\n1. `docker create` with environment\n2. `docker cp` project files to `/workspace/`\n3. `docker cp` override files from `.cloche/overrides/`\n4. `docker cp` Claude auth files (`.claude/`, `.claude.json`)\n5. `docker start`\n\n**In Container**:\n1. Run as root\n2. `chown -R agent:agent /workspace`\n3. Remove host-side tools (`.serena`, etc.)\n4. `su agent -s /bin/sh` to execute agent as unprivileged user\n\n---\n\n## **13. KEY CLASSES & INTERFACES**\n\n### **13.1 Workflow Execution Engine**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor\n    status         StatusHandler\n    maxSteps       int\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n\ntype StatusHandler interface {\n    OnStepStart(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step)\n    OnStepComplete(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string)\n    OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run)\n}\n```\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Launch entry step\n2. Receive result via channel\n3. Look up wires and collects\n4. Launch targets in parallel\n5. Repeat until all branches reach `done` or `abort`\n\n---\n\n### **13.2 Host Executor**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string              // Main branch worktree\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher       // For workflow dispatch\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string              // `.cloche/<run-id>/output`\n    Wires         []domain.Wire\n    HostRunID     string              // Parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n}\n\nfunc (e *Executor) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error) {\n    switch step.Type {\n    case domain.StepTypeScript:\n        return e.executeScript(ctx, step)\n    case domain.StepTypeWorkflow:\n        return e.executeWorkflow(ctx, step)\n    case domain.StepTypeAgent:\n        return e.executeAgent(ctx, step)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **13.3 Protocol & Status**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/protocol/`\n\n```go\ntype StatusMessage struct {\n    Type      MessageType  // \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"log\", \"error\"\n    StepName  string\n    Result    string\n    Message   string\n    Timestamp time.Time\n}\n\nfunc ExtractResult(output []byte) (result string, cleanOutput []byte, found bool)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **14. SUMMARY TABLE: COMPONENT INTERACTIONS**\n\n| Component | Location | Purpose | Inputs | Outputs |\n|-----------|----------|---------|--------|---------|\n| **cloche (CLI)** | `cmd/cloche/` | User interface | Command args | gRPC requests |\n| **cloched (Daemon)** | `cmd/cloched/` | Orchestration | gRPC requests | Container lifecycle, SQLite state |\n| **cloche-agent (Container)** | `cmd/cloche-agent/` | Workflow execution | Workflow file, CLOCHE_RUN_ID | JSON status messages |\n| **Engine** | `internal/engine/` | Step graph execution | Workflow DSL, StepExecutor | Run state transitions |\n| **Host Executor** | `internal/host/` | Host step execution | Steps, project dir | Shell exit codes, step outputs |\n| **Agent Adapters** | `internal/adapters/agents/` | Step-level execution | Step config, prompt | Result markers, output files |\n| **Docker Adapter** | `internal/adapters/docker/` | Container lifecycle | ContainerConfig | Container ID, logs |\n| **SQLite Store** | `internal/adapters/sqlite/` | Persistence | Run objects | CRUD operations |\n| **DSL Parser** | `internal/dsl/` | Configuration parsing | `.cloche` files | Workflow objects |\n| **Config Loader** | `internal/config/` | Configuration | TOML files, env vars | Config structs |\n\n---\n\n## **CONCLUSION**\n\nCloche is a sophisticated system for autonomous code generation with:\n\n1. **Three-tier architecture**: CLI → Daemon → Containers/Host\n2. **Flexible workflow execution**: Both container-based (agent) and host-based (orchestration)\n3. **Comprehensive state management**: SQLite + in-memory tracking + on-disk outputs\n4. **Result extraction & wiring**: JSON path-based environment variables between steps\n5. **Intelligent retries & fallbacks**: Max attempts, agent command fallback chains\n6. **Orchestration loop**: Automatic task assignment with deduplication and concurrency control\n7. **Extensible agents**: Generic commands, Claude Code prompts, or custom implementations\n8. **Unified logging**: Structured status messages, per-step logs, and permanent history\n\nAll paths are absolute and context is efficiently managed through environment variables, file-based outputs, and the SQLite store."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac89566dfcb904141 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 99719\ntool_uses: 43\nduration_ms: 122061</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e0bd824-184f-4257-9f99-c6d8b7efff47","uuid":"6b04211e-0246-455b-a2b6-5117939f63c9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall directory structure (ls the top-level, cmd/, internal/, etc.)\n2. The CLI commands structure in cmd/cloche/ - how subcommands are registered\n3. The domain types in internal/domain/ - especially Run, Step, Result types\n4. The ports interfaces in internal/ports/ - especially RunStore\n5. The host workflow executor in internal/host/\n6. The agent adapter in internal/adapters/ - how steps are executed\n7. How environment variables are set up for container runs and host runs\n8. Any existing context or state management for runs\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely.","agentId":"ac89566dfcb904141","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me create a comprehensive analysis document:\n\n## Cloche Project Structure and Architecture - Comprehensive Exploration\n\nBased on a thorough examination of the codebase, here's the complete technical overview of the Cloche system:\n\n---\n\n## **1. OVERALL PROJECT STRUCTURE**\n\n### Top-Level Directory Layout\n```\n/workspace/\n├── cmd/                      # Binary entry points (3 binaries)\n│   ├── cloche/              # CLI client (short-lived)\n│   ├── cloched/             # Daemon (long-running)\n│   └── cloche-agent/        # Container entrypoint (autonomous)\n├── internal/                # Core application logic\n│   ├── domain/              # Domain types (Run, Step, Workflow)\n│   ├── ports/               # Interface definitions (RunStore, ContainerRuntime, etc.)\n│   ├── adapters/            # Concrete implementations\n│   ├── host/                # Host workflow executor\n│   ├── engine/              # Workflow execution engine\n│   ├── dsl/                 # DSL parser & lexer\n│   ├── config/              # Configuration loading\n│   ├── agent/               # Agent runner for container\n│   ├── protocol/            # Result markers & status messages\n│   └── logstream/           # Unified log streaming\n├── .cloche/                 # Project-specific config\n│   ├── develop.cloche       # Container workflows\n│   ├── host.cloche          # Host orchestration workflows\n│   ├── config.toml          # Project configuration\n│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image definition\n│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates\n│   └── overrides/           # Files to override in container\n├── api/                     # gRPC protobuf definitions (auto-generated)\n├── docs/                    # Documentation\n├── examples/                # Example projects\n└── go.mod / go.sum          # Go dependencies\n```\n\n---\n\n## **2. THE THREE BINARIES**\n\n### **2.1 `cloche` (CLI Client)**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n**Design**: Short-lived CLI that connects to daemon via gRPC over Unix socket or TCP.\n\n**Commands**:\n- `init` - Initialize a Cloche project (no daemon needed)\n- `health` - Show project health (no daemon needed)\n- `run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]` - Launch workflow\n- `status <run-id>` - Check run status\n- `logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]` - Stream logs\n- `poll <run-id>` - Wait for completion\n- `list [--all]` - List recent runs\n- `stop <run-id>` - Stop running workflow\n- `delete <container-or-run-id>` - Delete retained container\n- `loop [--max <n>]` / `loop stop` - Manage orchestration loop\n- `shutdown` - Shut down daemon\n\n**gRPC Connection**:\n- Default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`\n- Configurable via `CLOCHE_ADDR` environment variable\n- Uses insecure credentials (local socket)\n\n---\n\n### **2.2 `cloched` (Daemon)**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n**Design**: Long-running server that manages container lifecycle, persists state, and executes host workflows.\n\n**Key Responsibilities**:\n1. **Listens on gRPC** (configurable via `CLOCHE_LISTEN`, default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n2. **HTTP Dashboard** (optional, via `CLOCHE_HTTP`, default: none)\n3. **SQLite Store** (configurable via `CLOCHE_DB`, default: `cloche.db`)\n4. **Container Runtime** (Docker or local, configurable via `CLOCHE_RUNTIME`)\n5. **Auto-run Active Projects** - At startup, scans for projects with `active = true` and runs their host workflows\n6. **Evolution Trigger** - Optional self-improvement system triggered after runs\n\n**Key Classes**:\n- `ClocheServer` (gRPC server implementation in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n  - Implements `RunWorkflow()`, `ListRuns()`, `GetStatus()`, `StreamLogs()`, etc.\n  - Manages run tracking via in-memory `map[string]string` (runID → containerID)\n  - Manages orchestration loops via `map[string]*host.Loop` (projectDir → Loop)\n\n---\n\n### **2.3 `cloche-agent` (Container Entrypoint)**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n\n**Design**: Autonomous agent that runs inside container, parses workflow DSL, and executes steps.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Receives workflow file path as arg: `cloche-agent /workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche`\n2. Reads `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` from environment (set by daemon before container start)\n3. Creates `RunnerConfig` and `Runner`\n4. Parses workflow DSL (container location)\n5. Creates adapters:\n   - `generic.Adapter` - for `script` and `agent` steps with `run` config\n   - `prompt.Adapter` - for `agent` steps with `prompt` config\n6. Sets up unified log stream and status writer\n7. Runs workflow via `engine.Engine`\n8. Emits JSON status messages to stdout (parsed by daemon)\n\n---\n\n## **3. DOMAIN TYPES** (`/workspace/internal/domain/`)\n\n### **3.1 Run State Machine**\n**File**: `run.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunState string\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState\n    ActiveSteps    []string              // Currently executing steps\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution      // Complete history\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string                // Absolute path to project root\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string                // Docker container ID (if container run)\n    BaseSHA        string                // Git HEAD at run start\n    ContainerKept  bool                  // true if container retained after completion\n    Title          string                // One-line summary of work\n    IsHost         bool                  // true for host workflow runs\n    ParentRunID    string                // ID of parent host run (for child container runs)\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string                  // Output state for results\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `NewRun(id, workflowName)` - Create new run\n- `Start()` - Transition to Running, set StartedAt\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)` - Add to ActiveSteps, create StepExecution\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` - Remove from ActiveSteps, complete StepExecution\n- `Complete(state)` - Transition to terminal state, set CompletedAt\n- `Fail(msg)` - Mark as failed with error message\n\n---\n\n### **3.2 Workflow & Step Types**\n**File**: `workflow.go`\n\n```go\ntype StepType string\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    = \"agent\"      // LLM or script-based agent\n    StepTypeScript   = \"script\"     // Shell command\n    StepTypeWorkflow = \"workflow\"   // Dispatch container workflow (host only)\n)\n\ntype WorkflowLocation string\nconst (\n    LocationContainer = \"container\"  // Runs inside Docker\n    LocationHost      = \"host\"       // Runs on host machine\n)\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType\n    Results []string                 // Declared outcomes (e.g., \"success\", \"fail\", \"needs_review\")\n    Config  map[string]string        // Step-specific config\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire                 // Result routing\n    Collects  []Collect              // Fanin synchronization\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string      // Workflow-level config (e.g., \"container.image\")\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string\n    Result    string\n    To        string\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping        // Environment variable extraction\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n    EnvVar string\n    Path   OutputPath                // JSON path navigation\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment           // Field access or array indexing\n}\n```\n\n**Key Workflow Config Keys**:\n- Container-level: `container.image`, `container.agent_command`, `container.agent_args`\n- Host-level: `host.agent_command`, `host.agent_args`\n\n**Step Config Keys**:\n- `prompt` - Prompt template (agent steps)\n- `run` - Shell command (script/agent steps)\n- `agent_command` - Agent fallback chain (comma-separated)\n- `agent_args` - Explicit agent arguments\n- `results` - Declared result names (redundant with Step.Results)\n- `max_attempts` - Retry limit\n- `timeout` - Step timeout (e.g., \"30m\")\n- `feedback` - Include validation output in agent prompt\n- `workflow_name` - Workflow to dispatch (host only)\n- `prompt_step` - Override previous step for prompt source\n\n---\n\n### **3.3 Run ID Generation**\n**File**: `namegen.go`\n\n```go\n// Format: <workflow>-<adjective>-<noun>-<hex>\n// Example: develop-swift-oak-a1b2\nfunc GenerateRunID(workflowName string) string {\n    adj := adjectives[mathrand.Intn(len(adjectives))]\n    noun := nouns[mathrand.Intn(len(nouns))]\n    var b [2]byte\n    rand.Read(b[:])\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s-%s-%s\", workflowName, adj, noun, hex.EncodeToString(b[:]))\n}\n```\n\nAdjectives: swift, bright, calm, dark, eager, fair, grand, happy, keen, lush, bold, cool, deft, firm, glad, warm, wild, wise, crisp, fresh, light, quick, sharp, quiet, vivid, brave, clear, gentle, proud, steady\n\nNouns: oak, elm, fox, hawk, lake, pine, reef, sage, vale, wolf, bear, cove, dale, fern, glen, hare, jade, lark, moss, nest, peak, reed, star, tide, vine, birch, brook, crane, drift, flint\n\n---\n\n## **4. PORTS & ADAPTERS** (Hexagonal Architecture)\n\n### **4.1 RunStore Interface**\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\n// SQLite Adapter: /workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go\n```\n\n**Database Schema** (SQLite):\n- `runs` table: id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id\n- `step_executions` table: id, run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n- `log_files` table: id, run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at\n- `merge_queue` table: run_id, branch, project, status, enqueued_at, completed_at\n- `evolution_log` table: id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, created_at, classification, changes_json, knowledge_delta\n\n---\n\n### **4.2 ContainerRuntime Interface**\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`\n\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ContainerConfig struct {\n    Image        string\n    WorkflowName string\n    ProjectDir   string\n    NetworkAllow []string\n    RunID        string\n    Cmd          []string              // Default: [\"cloche-agent\", WorkflowName]\n}\n\n// Docker Adapter: /workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go\n// Local Adapter: /workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go\n```\n\n---\n\n### **4.3 AgentAdapter Interface**\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Implementations**:\n- `prompt.Adapter` - Wraps Claude Code or other agents\n- `generic.Adapter` - Wraps shell scripts\n\n---\n\n## **5. WORKFLOW EXECUTION MODEL**\n\n### **5.1 Container Workflow Execution (Daemon → Container → Agent)**\n\n**Flow**:\n1. User: `cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"...\"`\n2. CLI → gRPC: `RunWorkflow()`\n3. Daemon: Creates Run (pending), launches background goroutine\n4. Background: Ensures image, starts container via Docker\n5. Container:\n   - Copies `/workspace/` from host\n   - Applies `.cloche/overrides/` on top\n   - Copies Claude auth files (`.claude/`, `.claude.json`)\n   - Runs as root, then `su agent -s /bin/sh` for safety\n   - Executes: `cloche-agent /workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche`\n6. Agent (in container):\n   - Parses DSL\n   - Walks step graph via `engine.Engine`\n   - For each step: executes via appropriate adapter\n   - Emits JSON status messages to stdout\n7. Daemon: Reads status messages, persists Run state to SQLite\n8. Daemon: When container exits, extracts `.cloche/output/` to host\n9. Daemon: Creates git branch `cloche/<run-id>` with results\n10. Run transitions to terminal state\n\n---\n\n### **5.2 Host Workflow Execution (Daemon → Host Steps)**\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Daemon starts (or via `cloche loop` command)\n2. Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` - may contain multiple workflows (main, finalize, etc.)\n3. Creates `Runner` with callbacks\n4. Runner executes via `Executor.Execute()` for each step type:\n   - **Script**: Shell command on host machine\n   - **Workflow**: Dispatches container workflow, blocks until complete\n   - **Agent**: Calls prompt adapter on host (Claude Code)\n5. Step outputs stored in `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n6. Wires pass outputs as environment variables to next steps\n\n---\n\n## **6. STEP EXECUTION & ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES**\n\n### **6.1 Container Run Environment**\n\n**Set by Daemon (Docker)**:\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<run-id>` - Passed via `-e` to `docker create`\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` - Passed if set on host\n- Additional via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` env var (comma-separated KEY=VALUE)\n\n**Set by Container Init Script**:\n- None beyond above\n\n**Available to Agent Steps**:\n- From step config: `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `prompt`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`\n- From workflow config: `container.agent_command`, `container.agent_args`\n\n---\n\n### **6.2 Host Run Environment**\n\n**Set by Executor for Script Steps**:\n```go\ncmd.Env = append(os.Environ(),\n    \"CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR=\"+e.ProjectDir,          // Always project root\n    \"CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT=\"+e.stepOutputPath(step.Name),\n    \"CLOCHE_TASK_ID=\"+e.TaskID,                  // If set by daemon loop\n    \"CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT=\"+prevOutput,            // Previous step output\n    ...mappedEnvVars...                          // From output mappings\n)\n```\n\n**Available to Agent Steps (Host)**:\n- From `Agent` adapter config: `agent_command`, `agent_args`\n- From step config: `prompt`, `prompt_step`\n- Run ID written to: `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n\n---\n\n### **6.3 Output Mappings & Environment Variables**\n\n**Mechanism**: Wires can define `OutputMap` to extract step output as env vars for next step.\n\n**Example DSL**:\n```\nstep1 -> success -> step2 {\n  env: MY_DATA { .result }        // Extract JSON field\n}\n```\n\n**Path Evaluation**: JSONPath-like syntax in `OutputPath.Evaluate()`\n- No segments: return raw output as string\n- `.field`: object field access\n- `[index]`: array indexing\n- Supports nested: `.users[0].name`\n\n---\n\n### **6.4 Result Markers**\n\n**Format**: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` on its own line (anywhere in output)\n\n**Extraction** (`protocol.ExtractResult()`):\n- Scans all output lines\n- Keeps last CLOCHE_RESULT marker encountered\n- Strips all marker lines from clean output\n- Returns: (resultName, cleanOutput, found)\n\n**Usage**:\n- Script: Echo marker to indicate non-standard result\n- Agent: Built into prompt instructions\n\n---\n\n## **7. LOG SYSTEM**\n\n### **7.1 Unified Log (Container)**\n**File**: `.cloche/<run-id>/full.log` (created by agent via `logstream.Writer`)\n\n**Contents**: Structured log entries combining:\n- Status markers (step started/completed)\n- Script output\n- LLM output (from Claude Code)\n\n---\n\n### **7.2 Per-Step Logs (Container)**\n**Files**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.log`\n\n**Contents**: \n- Scripts: Combined stdout/stderr (without result marker)\n- Agents: Raw output from agent command\n\n---\n\n### **7.3 Container Full Log**\n**File**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/container.log`\n\n**Contents**: Full `docker logs` output (unfiltered, all steps)\n\n---\n\n### **7.4 History Log (Host)**\n**File**: `.cloche/history.log` (permanent record)\n\n**Format**:\n```\n[2026-03-11T21:18:00Z] workflow:start develop\n\n[2026-03-11T21:18:15Z] step:plan result:success\n  | Generated 3 ideas\n  | 1. Add feature X\n  | 2. Fix bug Y\n\n[2026-03-11T21:18:20Z] step:implement result:success (agent)\n\n[2026-03-11T21:20:00Z] workflow:end develop result:succeeded\n```\n\n---\n\n## **8. ORCHESTRATION LOOP (Host Workflow Automation)**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n### **8.1 Three-Phase Loop**\n\n```\nLoop:\n  1. List Tasks (via list-tasks workflow)\n     └─ Returns: []{id, status, title, description, metadata}\n  \n  2. For each open task (up to MaxConcurrent):\n     └─ Run main workflow (passes CLOCHE_TASK_ID)\n  \n  3. After main completes:\n     └─ Run finalize workflow (receives mainResult outcome)\n\n  Deduplication: Don't re-assign same task within DedupTimeout (default: 5min)\n```\n\n### **8.2 Legacy Loop**\n\n```\nLoop:\n  1. (Optional) List tasks via TaskAssigner\n  2. For each open task (up to MaxConcurrent):\n     └─ Run single workflow (passes CLOCHE_TASK_ID)\n  3. (No finalize phase)\n```\n\n### **8.3 Configuration**\n\n```go\ntype LoopConfig struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MaxConcurrent int\n    StaggerDelay  time.Duration     // Delay between consecutive launches\n    DedupTimeout  time.Duration     // Task reassignment suppression window\n}\n```\n\n**Config Source** (`.cloche/config.toml`):\n```toml\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 2\nstagger_seconds = 1.0\nlist_tasks_command = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\ndedup_seconds = 300.0\n```\n\n---\n\n## **9. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (HOST & CONTAINER)**\n\n### **Key Variables**\n\n| Variable | Set By | Used By | Value |\n|----------|--------|---------|-------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | Daemon → Docker `-e` | Agent (reads, unsetsenv) | Generated run ID |\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Executor | Host scripts | Project root directory |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Executor | Host scripts | Path to step output file |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Executor | Host scripts | Task ID from loop |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Executor | Host scripts | Previous step output |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Container env | Agent runner | Fallback agent chain |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Host | Container | API key for Claude |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | Host | Docker | Comma-separated KEY=VALUE |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | Host | Docker | Comma-separated host:container paths |\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | User | CLI | gRPC server address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | User | CLI | HTTP dashboard address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | User | Daemon | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | User | Daemon | gRPC listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | User | Daemon | Default container image |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | User | Daemon | \"docker\" or \"local\" |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | User | Daemon | Path to cloche-agent binary |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | User | Daemon | Command for evolution |\n\n---\n\n## **10. CONTEXT & STATE MANAGEMENT**\n\n### **10.1 Run Context**\n\nEach run has:\n- **Run ID** - Unique identifier\n- **Workflow Name** - Entry point workflow\n- **Project Directory** - Absolute path to project\n- **Step Execution History** - All steps executed, their results, timing\n- **Output Directory** - `.cloche/<run-id>/output/` for step outputs\n- **BaseSHA** - Git HEAD when run started (for result branch creation)\n\n### **10.2 Per-Run State Storage**\n\n**On Disk**:\n- `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` - User prompt (for agent steps)\n- `.cloche/<run-id>/output/` - Step outputs, full log, container log\n- `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>` - Retry counter per step (container only)\n- `.cloche/history.log` - Permanent workflow event log (host only)\n\n**In SQLite**:\n- `runs` table - Run metadata\n- `step_executions` table - Execution history\n- `log_files` table - Log file index\n\n**In Memory (Daemon)**:\n- `ClocheServer.runIDs` - Run ID → Container ID mapping\n- `ClocheServer.loops` - Project Dir → Orchestration Loop\n\n---\n\n### **10.3 Output Path Conventions**\n\n```\nproject-root/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── <run-id>/\n│   │   ├── prompt.txt                  # Agent prompt input\n│   │   └── output/\n│   │       ├── full.log                # Unified log (container only)\n│   │       ├── container.log           # Full docker logs\n│   │       ├── <step-name>.log         # Per-step output\n│   │       ├── llm-<step-name>.log     # Copy of agent step log\n│   │       ├── <step-name>.out         # Host executor step output\n│   │       ├── full.log                # Concatenated output (agent)\n│   │       └── merged-content.md       # Git merge result (host)\n│   ├── attempt_count/                  # Retry counters (container)\n│   │   └── <step-name>\n│   ├── output/                         # Legacy: per-step logs\n│   │   └── <step-name>.log\n│   └── history.log                     # Permanent event log (host)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **11. DSL PARSER & CONFIGURATION**\n\n### **11.1 DSL Syntax**\n\n**File**: `*.cloche` (e.g., `develop.cloche`, `host.cloche`)\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step plan {\n    type: agent\n    results: success, needs_clarification\n    prompt: file(\"prompts/plan.md\")\n  }\n\n  step implement {\n    type: agent\n    results: success, fail\n    prompt: file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    feedback: true\n    max_attempts: 3\n    timeout: 60m\n    agent_command: claude\n    agent_args: -p --verbose\n  }\n\n  step validate {\n    type: script\n    results: pass, fail\n    run: bash .cloche/scripts/validate.sh\n  }\n\n  plan -> success -> implement\n  implement -> success -> validate\n  plan -> needs_clarification -> done\n  validate -> pass -> done\n  validate -> fail -> abort\n\n  collect { all plan:success, implement:success, validate:pass } -> finalize\n\n  container {\n    image: cloche-agent:latest\n    agent_command: claude\n    agent_args: -p --verbose\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Parser Location**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `Parse(input, opts...)` - Parse single workflow\n- `ParseForContainer()` - Parse with container location\n- `ParseForHost()` - Parse with host location\n- `ParseAllForHost()` - Parse multiple workflows from host.cloche\n\n---\n\n### **11.2 Configuration File**\n\n**File**: `.cloche/config.toml` (per-project)\n\n```toml\nactive = true                           # Auto-run at daemon startup\n\n[daemon]\nlisten = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\nhttp = \"localhost:8080\"\nimage = \"cloche-agent:latest\"\ndb = \"cloche.db\"\nruntime = \"docker\"                      # or \"local\"\nagent_path = \"/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\"\nllm_command = \"claude code --service evolution\"\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = true\ndebounce_seconds = 30\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"               # low, medium, high\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 2\nstagger_seconds = 1.0\nlist_tasks_command = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\ndedup_seconds = 300.0\n```\n\n**Global Config**: `~/.config/cloche/config` (daemon defaults)\n\n---\n\n## **12. INITIALIZATION & STARTUP**\n\n### **12.1 Daemon Startup** (`cloched`)\n\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config` (or defaults)\n2. Initialize SQLite store (with WAL, busy_timeout, single connection)\n3. Sweep stale runs (mark pending/running as failed)\n4. Initialize container runtime (Docker or local)\n5. Create gRPC server\n6. Scan projects for `active = true`, auto-run host workflows\n7. Set up evolution trigger (if LLM command configured)\n8. Listen on gRPC and HTTP\n\n### **12.2 Container Start**\n\n**Docker**:\n1. `docker create` with environment\n2. `docker cp` project files to `/workspace/`\n3. `docker cp` override files from `.cloche/overrides/`\n4. `docker cp` Claude auth files (`.claude/`, `.claude.json`)\n5. `docker start`\n\n**In Container**:\n1. Run as root\n2. `chown -R agent:agent /workspace`\n3. Remove host-side tools (`.serena`, etc.)\n4. `su agent -s /bin/sh` to execute agent as unprivileged user\n\n---\n\n## **13. KEY CLASSES & INTERFACES**\n\n### **13.1 Workflow Execution Engine**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor\n    status         StatusHandler\n    maxSteps       int\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n\ntype StatusHandler interface {\n    OnStepStart(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step)\n    OnStepComplete(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string)\n    OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run)\n}\n```\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Launch entry step\n2. Receive result via channel\n3. Look up wires and collects\n4. Launch targets in parallel\n5. Repeat until all branches reach `done` or `abort`\n\n---\n\n### **13.2 Host Executor**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string              // Main branch worktree\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher       // For workflow dispatch\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string              // `.cloche/<run-id>/output`\n    Wires         []domain.Wire\n    HostRunID     string              // Parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n}\n\nfunc (e *Executor) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error) {\n    switch step.Type {\n    case domain.StepTypeScript:\n        return e.executeScript(ctx, step)\n    case domain.StepTypeWorkflow:\n        return e.executeWorkflow(ctx, step)\n    case domain.StepTypeAgent:\n        return e.executeAgent(ctx, step)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **13.3 Protocol & Status**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/protocol/`\n\n```go\ntype StatusMessage struct {\n    Type      MessageType  // \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"log\", \"error\"\n    StepName  string\n    Result    string\n    Message   string\n    Timestamp time.Time\n}\n\nfunc ExtractResult(output []byte) (result string, cleanOutput []byte, found bool)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **14. SUMMARY TABLE: COMPONENT INTERACTIONS**\n\n| Component | Location | Purpose | Inputs | Outputs |\n|-----------|----------|---------|--------|---------|\n| **cloche (CLI)** | `cmd/cloche/` | User interface | Command args | gRPC requests |\n| **cloched (Daemon)** | `cmd/cloched/` | Orchestration | gRPC requests | Container lifecycle, SQLite state |\n| **cloche-agent (Container)** | `cmd/cloche-agent/` | Workflow execution | Workflow file, CLOCHE_RUN_ID | JSON status messages |\n| **Engine** | `internal/engine/` | Step graph execution | Workflow DSL, StepExecutor | Run state transitions |\n| **Host Executor** | `internal/host/` | Host step execution | Steps, project dir | Shell exit codes, step outputs |\n| **Agent Adapters** | `internal/adapters/agents/` | Step-level execution | Step config, prompt | Result markers, output files |\n| **Docker Adapter** | `internal/adapters/docker/` | Container lifecycle | ContainerConfig | Container ID, logs |\n| **SQLite Store** | `internal/adapters/sqlite/` | Persistence | Run objects | CRUD operations |\n| **DSL Parser** | `internal/dsl/` | Configuration parsing | `.cloche` files | Workflow objects |\n| **Config Loader** | `internal/config/` | Configuration | TOML files, env vars | Config structs |\n\n---\n\n## **CONCLUSION**\n\nCloche is a sophisticated system for autonomous code generation with:\n\n1. **Three-tier architecture**: CLI → Daemon → Containers/Host\n2. **Flexible workflow execution**: Both container-based (agent) and host-based (orchestration)\n3. **Comprehensive state management**: SQLite + in-memory tracking + on-disk outputs\n4. **Result extraction & wiring**: JSON path-based environment variables between steps\n5. **Intelligent retries & fallbacks**: Max attempts, agent command fallback chains\n6. **Orchestration loop**: Automatic task assignment with deduplication and concurrency control\n7. **Extensible agents**: Generic commands, Claude Code prompts, or custom implementations\n8. **Unified logging**: Structured status messages, per-step logs, and permanent history\n\nAll paths are absolute and context is efficiently managed through environment variables, file-based outputs, and the SQLite store."}],"totalDurationMs":122061,"totalTokens":99719,"totalToolUseCount":43,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1848,"cache_read_input_tokens":89201,"output_tokens":8670,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1848},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
